<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99309046790178></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99309046790178><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99309046790178>RE: Newbie</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=99309046790178#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 20th 10:27 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>First things first, have you gotten all of your spells? some not well known research spells are great to have.&nbsp;&nbsp;Check your spells against casters realm list<br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Enchanter" target=_new>http://eq.castersrealm.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Enchanter</a><br><br>If you haven't and are having bad luck with not succeeding in creating your spells, buy a concordance of research and up your research that way (warning: money sapper from components if you want to raise it a lot)<br><br>Before battle you must make sure you have the right buffs on and keep them on throughout your fight and group members who need them.  breeze, sympathetic aura(yourself only to aid in mezzing), cloud, shielding for yourself, and endure magic(protection from mezzing yourself on aoe mezzes) are the basic spells you should try to always have on.  <br><br>The first battle should tell you if your group knows how to play with an enchanter or not.  If your tanks are not assisting the puller or if a number of other things happen you have to give them "the talk" in which probably the 2 most important points include you say to them:<br>"-always assist the puller<br>-if i try to mez one and it resists and comes after me, don't charge at it unless i ask for help, because most probably you'll break my mez<br>when i succeed in mezzing it a second later."<br><br>To help others, make sure you have a hotkey button that goes something like this (with enthrall being on oh say, the 5th slot)<br><br>/cast 5<br>/gsay "Attempting to MEZ %T do not attack it"<br><br>And make sure if you die or something happens where you change around your spells, to make sure that the /cast # command and the slot you have your enthrall spell in match up.  You don't want to accidentally gate yourself or something ;P<br><br>A hotkey like that is essential for enthrall (probably use the word mez instead of enthrall because most non enchanters don't know the names of the single target mezzes)  You don't necessarily need a hotkey button for the rest, maybe root... Some like to, others say that to many txt buttons linked with spells gives too much spam, but its a matter of what you like, really.<br><br>Some of what you cast will depend on what other classes you are grouped with.  For example later on you can ds, invigor, and high lvl runes, etc to try to lessen the impact of not having a druid/cleric.   <br><br>it sounds like you are doing great so far with tashing everything and quicknessing the tanks and knowing when and when not to use aoe mez.  The Tash line costs little, casts quick, and works well, and tanks love their crack just as much as we casters love ours(make sure you are using tashani and not tashan though)  Also debuffs are fine, the best one being tashani and then languid pace IMHO, but any more than that you should only do if you have extra mana and time on your hands, (unless you are camping one large spawn) because it is more efficient to buff your tanks, and usually your time is spent elsewhere.  Once a pull is inc, a good proccess would be this<br><br>if there is one mob pulled..<br>let the tank get in a taunt and a little damage so the mob won't aggro on you when you cast on it.  Tashani the mob then quickness tank and   languid pace the mob.  Nuke(sanity warp)/dot(choke) it if you have mana to burn.<br><br>if more than one comes...<br>immediately single enthrall the spares.  make sure everyone is assisting off of the tank or this will do nothing.  If one resists, tashani and enthrall again.  (or first tashani then enthrall... but you don't always have time for this method and it may aggro on you)If the mob hits you quickly and interrupts you a lot, color shift to stun him (casts fast) then enthrall him and the rest.  After the enthralling is done, tash the ones you haven't for future enthralls, or other spells against it.  Remember when something is enthralled you can debuff it all you want without breaking enthrall.  Now quickness the tank if he needs it and languid pace the one he's on and the rest.  Med and watch your text screen to see if an enthrall wears off or is broken and re-enthrall.  monitor everyone's health as well, which will give an indication if there has been an add.  When the tank gets down to the last or second to last one, feel free to nuke/dot if mana permits and everyone's buffs are good.<br><br><br>if there are quite a lot....<br>aoe mez first if you know you aren't attacking high magic resists mobs.  if one resists and gets on you, tashani it and enthrall.  If more than one get on you, colorshift/aoe mez--keep trying until you get it off. Run a bit away when you can(so you won't mez self with next aoe mez if you haven't mezzed yourself along with this first one), and tash them all, quickness the tank if mana permits, re aoe mez (mezmerization) and med.  This should have taken up a lot of your mana, and your number one priority is crowd control, so don't worry about debuffing(besides tash).  Root if you want and have mana a few out of the way ones so that when aoe mez wears off you can have extra time and maybe even enthrall it.  Med for future mezmerization/enthralls.  because this pull should have, brought you down significantly in mana (or will when its over) and you don't want the one your tank is on to possibly aggro on you especially if several enthralls/mezmerizations wear off... Don't forget too, single target mezzes(i.e. enthrall) doesn't stack with mezmerization.  <br><br>If ever there are problems, such as the tank can't taunt one off the cleric, and you don't have memory blur memorized, enthrall that one, and when the tank breaks mez, the mob will usually go on him instead of the cleric.  <br><br>if you are low on mana...<br>if a lot come, try to stand back enough to aoe mez to give your group a chance to live when they run or aoe mez then tash them all and med, redoing the aoe mez about every 20 seconds or so (lasts 24 seconds according to casters realm)<br><br>Although your mana will probably be nice now that you have breeze, try to make sure it is at least 2 bubbles at all times in case of an unexpected large pull or train. Quickness to tanks is a nice way to drain your mana ;) <br><br>If you have mana and time to burn...<br>-cast serpent sight on those who can't see well in the dark, it really does help them out more than you might think.<br>-illusion yourself as a troll to gain back more hit points per tick and save the cleric some mana<br>-benevolence a random npc (non-KOS)and bask in the love. :)<br>-aid the puller by calming a second monster so that you have an easier pull and no need/less need to enthrall<br>-cancel magic to get rid of those annoying ds's on MOB's<br>-root the ones you have mezzed so that if mez/enthrall wears off first you have more time to remez it.  <br>-rebuff yourself and the rest of your group<br>-rune the tank/yourself if the cleric is low on mana and you are in a dangerous spot<br>-if your tank usually pulls one or just if you have an extra slot open, put on your whirl till you hurl spell (nice stun) but be sure to always tashani first<br>-cast true north to get that stubborn divination skill up.<br>-chaotic feedback a group member so they can see the pretty sparkles and you can work on your evocation<br>-get yourself a pet  -nooo not an animation--, a real pet(have animations for soloing...fine, but in groups they just break mez too much).  Charm something (also tashani it) and help out your tank with /pet attack  or /pet guard here etc.<br><br>Here's a good list of spells to have mem'd<br>-gate<br>-quickness/languid pace<br>-root/dd/dot<br>-color flux<br>-mezmerization<br>-enthrall<br>-tashani<br>-changable buff/free spell, such as breeze, or whirl till you hurl if you want to see 'em spin ;)<br><br>i have to say too, that enchanters get a vast array of spells, a great selection to chose from, especially in the higher levels when you'll get more lines of spells, and different types of illusions. <br>People probably say you are brave to start out with an enchanter because it is hard to master the art of crowd control well, especially since it is so important, and can be the difference between life and death for your group in so many instances.  <br><br>Enchanters are one of the most sought after classes in the game.  Have fun with the array of options you have, the options will grow more as you level, although of course there are some spells you will use most, there are usually some helpful bonuses from obscure spells for your group (i.e. serpent sight) Of course what i gave are just some things that have worked for me, and i'm sure i'm missing something, but refine it to fit your own personality :)<br><br>Xaria Soulchanger<br>38 Enchantress of the Druzzil Ro server<br>Paragons of Conquest<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
