	   <tr><td colspan=2>After reading your comment on not EVER using AE mez, I was looking down for your tag to see how LOW of a level you were.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stunning to see that by level 56, you haven't learned all of your capabilities, especially from a LEVEL !16! spell!  AE is VERY useful.  If you can't deal with mezzing the resists quickly if you get any, then you're not a very quick enchanter at all, but rather a very lazy one.  There are some mobs that have very low magic resist, but attack VERY hard.  So you AE mez them, so your tanks don't get wiped out in 5 seconds.<br><br>42 Enchanter, Helkiroo, High elf, M. Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
